      "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">A nutritionist is calculating the daily caloric needs for a 60kg individual who engages in sedentary work. Considering the factors that influence energy requirements, such as body weight and activity level, what is the approximate daily calorie requirement for this person?</span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q4344242",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 29979,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        1
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\"><strong>Ans. C) 2000 kcal</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\"><strong>The daily caloric requirement for an individual depends on several factors:</strong></span></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">Body weight and composition</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">Age and sex</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">Activity level (sedentary, moderate, heavy labor)</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">Physiological states (growth, pregnancy, illness)</span><br>&nbsp;</li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\"><strong>For a sedentary adult, the general estimate is 30 kcal/kg/day of body weight.</strong></span><br>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\"><strong>For a 60 kg sedentary adult:</strong></span></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">Basal requirement = 60 × 30 = 1800 kcal/day</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">Add 10% for the specific dynamic action (SDA) of food = 1800 × 0.10 = 180 kcal</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">Total energy requirement ≈ 1980–2000 kcal/day</span><br>&nbsp;</li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\"><strong>This approximation aligns with dietary planning recommendations for adults with minimal physical exertion.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\"><strong>Other Options:</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\"><strong>Other Options:</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\"><strong>Option A) 1000 kcal: </strong>Too low — would only meet basal metabolic needs for a much smaller or inactive individual, not adequate for daily maintenance.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\"><strong>Option&nbsp;B) 1500 kcal: </strong>Still below the estimated requirement for a 60 kg adult, even in a sedentary state.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\"><strong>Option&nbsp;D) 2500 kcal: </strong>For a sedentary person, this would likely exceed maintenance needs.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\"><strong>Educational Objective:</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">The approximate daily caloric requirement for a sedentary adult weighing 60kg is around 2000 kcal.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\"><strong>Ref</strong>: DM Vasudevan 9/e: p 538.</span></p>",
